              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tx32/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>The payments have been so tardy that I find myself unwarranted<lb/> to send you an\n\t\t\t\torder for books. I feel my inclination to do so<lb/> much greater than my ability,\n\t\t\t\tstill if you like to send a couple<lb/> of sets &amp; a few Dailys I will try what I\n\t\t\t\tcan do with them<lb/> I will remit you per <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> for the\n\t\t\t\tset sold <persName>Mr S Hymans</persName> (<add>?</add><lb/> west to the Dame\n\t\t\t\t\t<add>?</add>—perhaps a line from you may be effective)<lb/> though I\n\t\t\t\t\t<sic>dont</sic> think he will pay for it just yet—he has frequently<lb/> been\n\t\t\t\tasked. I want no disconnect on it thinking it scarcely<lb/> fair for you to pay it\n\t\t\t\ton such long credits. I will also remit<lb/> you for<lb/>\n\t\t\t\t<date>Kipoor</date> &amp; 2 Daily. The copies of the <persName>Soto</persName> Bible\n\t\t\t\tsent<lb/> out I know nothing about. <persName>Mr J.</persName> sent them out and I\n\t\t\t\tbelieve<lb/> had tried to collect the amounts, but as I have not deemed<lb/> myself\n\t\t\t\tauthorized to interfere I have refrained from pressing<lb/> payment, but if you send\n\t\t\t\tme a line (which I can show) requesting<lb/> me to obtain payment for you I think I\n\t\t\t\tmay be able to do<lb/> something for you. With respect to the Occident it is not\n\t\t\t\tmy<lb/> fault if it has not more readers here, for although I may<lb/> have deemed\n\t\t\t\tits conduct towards me not over generous, I have<lb/> always recommended it as the\n\t\t\t\t\tsuperb<add>?</add> Jewish magazine, but<lb/> my people are very like their\n\t\t\t\tbrethren <add>?</add> side the lines<lb/>\n\t\t\t\t<hi rend=\"underline\">the Journal</hi>, ledger &amp; cash Book have great interest as\n\t\t\t\tserious<lb/> reading while for lighter moments the Book of Kings (&amp;\n\t\t\t\t<add>?</add>)<lb/> obtain their share of attention. Do you intend to <add>?</add>\n\t\t\t\tyour<lb/> weekly?</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(4)\">I am dear sir</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(5)\">Yours truly</p>\n\t\t\t<p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n\t\t\t\t<persName role=\"author\">Abraham de Sola</persName>\n\t\t\t</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tx32/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
